<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3165a3e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1837"><num value="1837">§ 1837.</num><heading> Duration of health care and benefits provided</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall provide a covered child with health care and benefits under this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3165a3f-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1837/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> for the duration of the life of the child; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc3165a40-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1837/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> notwithstanding any death of a parent of the child that precedes the death of the child.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idc3165a41-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/118/18/s1/b">Pub. L. 118–18, § 1(b)</ref>, <date date="2023-10-06">Oct. 6, 2023</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/137/104">137 Stat. 104</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
